obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (71423)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71423&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Central Provinces Court`
  line `of Wards Act, 1899.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the territories for the time being administered by the Local Government of the Central`
  line `Provinces; and`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force at once.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (71424)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71424&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(a) the expression "Government ward" means any person of whose property, or of whose person`
  line `and property, the Court of Wards may, for the time being, have the superintendence under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "land" includes the rights of a land-holder in respect of the land of which he is the malguzar or`
  line `zamindar or the muafidar, jagirdar, ubaridar or other assignee of land-revenue, or in which he is`
  line `interested; and`
  line
  line `(c) "land-holder" means a malguzar as defined in the Central Provinces Land-revenue Act, 1881,`
  line `XVIII of 1881, and the zamindar of any zamindari in a Scheduled District, and includes a muafidar,`
  line `jagirdar, ubaridar or other assignee of land-revenue, and any person not hereinbefore specified who is`
  line `interested in land and belongs to a class of which the Local Government, with the previous sanction`
  line `of the Governor General in Council, has declared the members to be land-holders for the purposes of`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (71425)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Commissioner to be Court of Wards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71425&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 9, the Commissioner`
  line `shall be the Court of Wards for the limits of his division.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (71426)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Superintendence by Court of Wards of property of disqualified landholder.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71426&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Court of`
  line `Wards may, with the previous sanction of the Local Government, assume the superintendence of the`
  line `property of any land-holder owning land within the local limits of its jurisdiction who is disqualified to`
  line `manage his property.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (71427)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Land-holders to be deemed disqualified in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71427&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The following persons shall, for`
  line `the purposes of section 4, be deemed to be disqualified to manage their own property, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) minors;`
  line
  line `(b) persons adjudged by a competent Civil Court to be of unsound mind and incapable of managing`
  line `their affairs; and`
  line
  line `(c) persons declared by the Local Government to be incapable of managing their property owing`
  line to--
  line
  line `(i) any physical or mental defect or infirmity;`
  line
  line `(ii) their having been convicted of a non-bailable offence and being unfitted by vice or bad`
  line `character; or`
  line
  line `(iii) their being females.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit shall be brought in any Civil Court in respect of any declaration made by the Local`
  line `Government under sub-section (1), clause (c).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (71428)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Superintendence by Court of Wards on application of proprietor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71428&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any land-holder may`
  line `apply to the Local Government to have his property placed under the superintendence of the Court of Wards,`
  line `and the Local Government may on such application, if it thinks it expedient in the public interests, order`
  line `the Court of Wards to assume the superintendence of the property.`
  line
  line `(2) An order made by the Local Government under sub-section (1) shall be sufficient to authorize the`
  line `Court of Wards to assume the superintendence of the property referred to therein, and no suit shall be`
  line `brought in any Civil Court in respect of any such order.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (71429)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Temporary provisions for custody of heirs and protection of property in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71429&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever the Court of Wards receives information that any land-holder has died and has reason to`
  line `believe that the heir of the land-holder is a person who is, or should be adjudged or declared to be,`
  line `disqualified under section 5, the Court may--`
  line
  line `(a) take such steps and make such order for the temporary custody and protection of the property`
  line `inherited as it thinks fit; and,`
  line
  line `(b) if the heir is a minor, direct that the person (if any) having the custody of the minor, shall`
  line `produce him or cause him to be produced at such place and time and before such person as the Court`
  line `may appoint, and make such order for the temporary custody and protection of the minor as it thinks`
  line `fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where the minor is a female and belongs to a class the females of which do not usually`
  line `appear in public, her production shall be required only in accordance with the manners and customs of the`
  line country.
  line
  line `(2) Whenever the Court of Wards proceeds under this section, it shall forthwith report its action for the`
  line `information of the Local Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (71430)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Superintendence by Court of Wards of person of disqualified landholder.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71430&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Where the Court`
  line `of Wards assumes the superintendence of the property of a minor or of a person who has been adjudged by`
  line `a competent Civil Court to be of unsound mind and incapable of managing his affairs, it may, with the`
  line `previous sanction of the Local Government, assume the superintendence of his person also:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall authorize the Court of Wards to assume the superintendence`
  line `of the person of a female who is married to a man of full age and is in his custody.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (71465)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Superintendence by Court of Wards where disqualified landholder owns land in more than one division`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71465&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Where a land-holder owns land within two or more divisions, such one only of the Courts`
  line `of Wards as the Local Government may determine in this behalf shall assume the superintendence of the`
  line `property, or of the person and property, of the land-holder.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (71466)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Assumption of superintendence to be notified and to extend to whole of Government ward’s property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71466&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever the Court of Wards assumes the superintendence of the property of any person`
  line `under this Act, the fact of such assumption, and the date on which it was sanctioned by the Local`
  line `Government, shall be notified in the local official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(2) On and with effect from the date of such sanction, the whole of the property, moveable or`
  line `immoveable, of such person, whether the existence of any such property may be known to the said Court`
  line `or not, shall be deemed to be under the superintendence of the Court of Wards.`
  line
  line `(3) Any property which the Government ward may inherit subsequently to the date of such sanction,`
  line `shall also be deemed to be under the superintendence of the Court of Wards.`
  line
  line `(4) The Court of Wards may, in its discretion, assume, or refrain from assuming, the superintendence`
  line `of any property which the ward may acquire, otherwise than by inheritance subsequently to the date of such`
  line notification.
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (71433)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Barring of suits to contest authority to assume superintendence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71433&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `No suit shall be brought in`
  line `any Civil Court to contest the authority of the Court of Wards in respect of the property, or of the person`
  line `and property, of any person under this Act on the ground that such person was not, or is not, a land-holder`
  line `or a minor.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (71434)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Notices to claimants against Government ward.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71434&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the issue of a notification under`
  line `section 10, the Court of Wards shall publish in the local official Gazette and in such other manner as the`
  line `Local Government may, by general or special order, direct, a notice, in English and also in the vernacular,`
  line `calling upon all persons having claims against the Government ward or his immoveable property to submit`
  line `the same in writing to it within six months from the date of the publication of the notice aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such claim (other than a claim on the part of the Government) not submitted to the Court of`
  line `Wards in compliance with the provisions of sub-section (1), shall, save in the case provided for by`
  line `section 16, sub-section (2), clause (c), be deemed for all purposes and on all occasions, whether during the`
  line `continuance of the management or afterwards, to have been duly discharged:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the Court of Wards is satisfied that the claimant was unable to comply with the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (1), it may receive his claim at any time after the date of the expiry of the period`
  line `aforesaid, but any claim so received shall, notwithstanding any law, contract, decree or award to the`
  line `contrary, cease to carry interest from the date of the expiry of the period aforesaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (71435)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Claimants to furnish full particulars and documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71435&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every claimant submitting his claim`
  line `in compliance with the provisions of section 12, sub-section (1), shall furnish, along with his written`
  line `statement of claim, full particulars thereof, and shall, at the same time, produce all documents (including`
  line `entries in books of account) on which he relies to support his claim, together with a true copy of every such`
  line document.
  line
  line `(2) The Court of Wards shall, after making, for the purpose of identification, every original document`
  line `so produced and verifying the correctness of the copy, retain the copy and return the original to the claimant.`
  line
  line `(3) If any document, which is in the possession or under the control of the claimant, is not produced by`
  line `him as required by sub-section (1), the document shall not be admissible in evidence against the`
  line `Government ward, whether during the continuance of the management or afterwards, in any suit brought`
  line `by the claimant or by any person claiming under him.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (71436)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Stay of proceedings of Civil Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71436&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `If a Civil Court has directed any process of execution to`
  line `issue against any immoveable property of a Government ward or the rents thereof or any crops standing`
  line `thereon, the Court of Wards may, at any time within one year after the issue of a notification under section`
  line `10, apply to the Civil Court to stay proceedings in the matter of such process, and the Civil Court may, on`
  line `such terms regarding interest or compensation for delay as may appear to it to be just and reasonable, stay`
  line `such proceedings accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (71437)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Adjudication of claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71437&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of all claims submitted in compliance with the provisions`
  line `of sections 12 and 13, the Court of Wards shall proceed to investigate such claims and shall decide which`
  line `of them are to be wholly or partly admitted or wholly or partly rejected, as the case may be, and shall`
  line `communicate its decision in writing to each claimant concerned.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Court of Wards has admitted any claim under sub-section (1), it may make to the claimant`
  line `a proposal in writing for the reduction of the claim, or of the rate of interest to be paid in future, or of both;`
  line `and, if such proposal, or any modification of it, is accepted by the claimant and his acceptance is finally`
  line `recorded and attested by the Court of Wards or by any Revenue-officer not being below the rank of an`
  line `Assistant Commissioner whom the Local Government may, by general or special order, appoint in this`
  line `behalf, it shall be conclusively binding upon the claimant:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if when the superintendence of the property by the Court of Wards is relinquished or`
  line `otherwise terminates, any portion of the claim reduced as aforesaid is still unsatisfied, the claimant shall be`
  line `entitled to recover a sum bearing the same proportion to the original claim admitted under sub-section (1)`
  line `as the unsatisfied portion bears to the reduced claim.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), nothing in this section shall be construed to bar the`
  line `institution of a suit in a Civil Court for the recovery of a claim against a Government ward or his property`
  line `which has been submitted to and received by the Court of Wards:`
  line
  line `Provided that, no decision of the Court of Wards under this section shall be proved in any such suit as`
  line `against the defendant.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (71438)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Report of Chief Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71438&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) When all claims have been investigated under section 15,`
  line `the Court of Wards shall submit to the Local Government a schedule of the debts and liabilities of the`
  line `Government ward, and the Local Government may, when the estate appears to be involved beyond all hope`
  line `of extrication or for any other sufficient reason, by an order published in the Local official Gazette, direct`
  line `that, on a date to be fixed by the order, the superintendence of the property and person of the ward shall be`
  line `relinquished by the Court of Wards.`
  line
  line `(2) On the date so fixed--`
  line
  line `(a) the superintendence shall terminate;`
  line
  line `(b) the owner of the property under superintendence shall be restored to the possession thereof,`
  line `subject to any contracts entered into by the Court of Wards for the preservation or benefit of such`
  line property;
  line
  line `(c) the claims referred to in section 12, sub-section (2), shall revive.`
  line
  line `(3) In calculating the periods of limitation applicable to suits to recover and enforce debts and liabilities`
  line `revived under this section, the time during which such superintendence has continued shall be excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (71439)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Appointment, etc., of managers by Court of Wards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71439&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The Court of Wards may appoint a`
  line `manager of the property of any Government ward under its superintendence.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (71440)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Delegation of powers by Court of Wards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71440&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) With the general or special sanction of the Local`
  line `Government, the Court of Wards may, from time to time, delegate all or any of its powers to the Deputy`
  line `Commissioner of any district in which any part of the property of a Government ward is situated, or to`
  line `any other person whom it may appoint in this behalf; and may, at any time, with the like sanction, revoke`
  line `such delegation.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to any general or special orders of the Local Government, the Court of Wards may exercise`
  line `all or any powers conferred on it by this Act through the Deputy Commissioner of any district in which`
  line `any part of the property of a Government ward is situated, or through any other person whom it may appoint`
  line `in this behalf, and, subject to the like orders, any such Deputy Commissioner may exercise all or any powers`
  line `delegated to him under this Act through any Revenue-officer subordinate to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (71441)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Liabilities, etc., of managers and other servants of Court of Wards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71441&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every manager`
  line `appointed by the Court of Wards shall--`
  line
  line `(a) give such security as the Court thinks fit duly to account for what he receives in respect of the`
  line `rents and profits of the property under his management;`
  line
  line `(b) be entitled to such allowance as the Court thinks fit for his care and pains in the execution of`
  line `his duties; and`
  line
  line `(c) be responsible for any loss occasioned to the property under his management by his wilful`
  line `default or gross negligence.`
  line
  line `(2) Every manager or other servant of the Court of Wards shall be deemed a "public servantsbqts within`
  line `the meaning of sections 161, 162, 163, 164 and 165 of the Indian Penal Code (XLV of 1860); and in the`
  line `definition of "legal remuneration" contained in the said section 161, the word sbqtsGovernmentsbqts shall, for the`
  line `purposes of this sub-section, be deemed to include the Court of Wards.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (71442)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Power for Court of Wards to appoint guardians of certain Government wards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71442&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The Court of`
  line `Wards may appoint guardians for the care of the persons of Government wards whose persons are, for the`
  line `time being, under its superintendence.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (71443)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `General powers of Court of Wards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71443&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act and of any rules`
  line `thereunder, the Court of Wards--`
  line
  line `(a) may, of itself or through the manager (if any) appointed by it under this Act, do all such things`
  line `requisite for the proper care and management of any property, of which it assumes the superintendence`
  line `under this Act, as the owner of the property, if it were not under the superintendence of the Court of`
  line `Wards, might do for its care and management; and`
  line
  line `(b) may, of itself or through the guardian (if any) appointed by it under this Act, do, in respect of`
  line `the person of any Government ward whose person is, for the time being, under its superintendence, all`
  line `such things as may lawfully be done by a guardian.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (71444)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Custody, education and residence of certain Government wards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71444&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The Court of Wards may`
  line `pass such orders as it thinks fit in respect of the custody and residence of any Government ward whose`
  line `person is, for the time being, under its superintendence, and, when he is a minor, in respect of his education.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (71445)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Allowance for Government ward and his family.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71445&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The Court of Wards may, from time to time,`
  line `determine what sums shall be allowed in respect of the expenses of any Government ward and of his family`
  line `and dependants.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (71446)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Duties of Court of Wards or manager.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71446&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The Court of Wards, or the manager (if any) appointed`
  line `by it under this Act, shall manage the property of every Government ward under its superintendence or`
  line `under his management diligently and faithfully for the benefit of the Government ward, and shall in every`
  line `respect act to the best of its or his judgment for the Government ward's interest as if the property were its`
  line `or his own.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (71448)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Powers of Court of Wards as to property of Government wards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71448&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The Court of Wards may let`
  line `the whole or any part of the property of any Government ward under its superintendence, and may, with`
  line `the previous sanction of the Local Government, mortgage, sell or exchange the whole or any part of such`
  line `property, and may do all such other acts as it may judge to be best for the benefit of the property and the`
  line `advantage of the Government ward.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (71449)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Notice of suit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71449&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `No suit relating to the person or property of any Government ward shall be brought`
  line `in any Civil Court until the expiration of two months after notice in writing, stating the name and place of`
  line `abode of the intending plaintiff, the cause of action and the relief claimed, has been delivered to, or left at`
  line `the office of, the Court of Wards; and the plaint shall contain a statement that such notice has been so`
  line `delivered or left:`
  line
  line `Provided that notice under this section shall not be required in the case of any suit the period of`
  line `limitation for which will expire within three months from the date of a notification issued under section 10,`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (71450)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Manager or Court of Wards to be next friend or guardian in suit by or against Government wards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71450&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `In every suit brought by or against a Government ward, the manager of the ward's property or, if`
  line `there is no manager, the Court of Wards having the superintendence of the ward's property shall be named`
  line `as the next friend or guardian for the suit, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (71451)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Payment of costs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71451&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `If, in any suit brought by or against a Government ward, any Civil Court`
  line `decrees any costs against the Government ward's next friend or guardian for the suit, the Court of Wards`
  line `shall cause the costs to be paid out of any property of the Government ward which may, for the time being,`
  line `be in its hands.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (71452)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Processes against Government ward to be served on next friend or guardian.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71452&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Every process`
  line `which may be issued out of any Civil or Revenue Court against any Government ward shall be served on`
  line `the Government ward's next friend or guardian for the suit.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (71453)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Authority of Court of Wards required in case of suits brought on behalf of Government wards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71453&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `No suit shall be brought, and no appeal in any suit shall be preferred, on behalf of any Government`
  line `ward unless it is authorized by an order in writing of the Court of Wards:`
  line
  line `Provided as follows:--`
  line
  line `(1) a manager may authorize a plaint to be filed in order to prevent a suit from being barred by the`
  line `law of limitation, but the suit shall not afterwards be proceeded with except under the sanction of the`
  line `Court of Wards;`
  line
  line `(2) a suit for arrears of rent may be brought on behalf of a Government ward, if authorized by an`
  line `order of the manager of the property on which the rent is due.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (71454)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Disabilities of a Government ward.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71454&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Government ward shall be incompetent to transfer or`
  line `create any charge on, or interest in, his property or any part thereof (except such interest as may be created`
  line `by a will made in accordance with section 32), or to enter into any contract which may involve him in`
  line `pecuniary liability; and no suit shall be brought in any Civil Court whereby to charge any person upon any`
  line `promise made after he has ceased to be a Government ward to pay any debt contracted during the period`
  line `when he was a Government ward, or upon any ratification made after he has ceased to be a Government`
  line `ward of any promise or contract made during the period aforesaid, whether there is or is not any new`
  line `consideration for such promise or ratification.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to affect the capacity of a Government ward to enter into a`
  line `contract of marriage:`
  line
  line `Provided that a Government ward shall not incur, in connection with such a contract, any pecuniary`
  line `liability, except such as, having regard to the personal law to which he is subject and to his rank and`
  line `circumstances, the Court of Wards may, in writing, declare to be reasonable.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (71455)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Consent of Local Government necessary to adoptions or wills made by Government wards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71455&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `No adoption by a Government ward, and no written or verbal permission to adopt given by a Government`
  line `ward, or will made by a Government ward, shall be valid without the consent of the Local Government`
  line `obtained, either previously or subsequently to the adoption or to the giving of the permission, or the making`
  line `of the will, on application made to it through the Court of Wards.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (71456)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Procedure when succession to Government ward's property is disputed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71456&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Whenever, on the`
  line `death of any Government ward, the succession to his property or any part thereof is disputed, the Court of`
  line `Wards may, with the previous sanction of the Local Government, either direct that the property or the part`
  line `thereof be made over to any person claiming the property, or retain the superintendence of the property`
  line `until one of the claimants has established his claim to the same in a competent Civil Court, or institute a`
  line `suit of interpleader against all the claimants.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (71457)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Withdrawal of superintendence of Court of Wards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71457&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Court of Wards may, with the`
  line `sanction of the Local Government, at any time withdraw its superintendence from the person or property,`
  line `or both, of a Government ward, and shall withdraw its superintendence as soon as,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a person disqualified under clause (a) of section 5, sub-section (1), he attains his`
  line majority;
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a person disqualified under clause (b) of the same, he ceases to be of unsound`
  line `mind and incapable of managing his affairs;`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of a person disqualified under sub-clause (i) of clause (c) of the same, his physical`
  line `or mental defect or infirmity is removed or ceases:`
  line
  line `Provided as follows:--`
  line
  line `(i) whenever a Government ward lies or ceases to be disqualified and his property is still`
  line `encumbered with debts and liabilities, the Court of Wards may, with the previous sanction of the Local`
  line `Government, either release such property or retain it under its superintendence until such debts and`
  line `liabilities have been discharged; and,`
  line
  line `(ii) if one or more of the proprietors of a property remain disqualified, although another or others`
  line `may have ceased to be disqualified, the Court of Wards may, with the previous sanction of the Local`
  line `Government, retain the whole of the property under its superintendence, paying any proprietor who has`
  line `ceased to be disqualified, the surplus income accruing from his share of the estate.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any question arises as to whether the superintendence of the Court of Wards should be`
  line `withdrawn from any person or property, or both, under clause (a), or from any property under clause (c),`
  line `of sub-section (1), the decision of the Local Government thereon shall be final, and no suit shall be brought`
  line `in any Civil Court in respect of such decision.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (71458)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Appointment of guardian in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71458&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, in exercise of the power conferred by`
  line `section 34, the Court of Wards decides to withdraw its superintendence from the person and property of`
  line `any minor, it shall, before such withdrawal, by an order in writing, appoint some person to be guardian of`
  line `the person or property, or both, of the minor, and such appointment shall take effect from the date of such`
  line release.
  line
  line `(2) In appointing a guardian under this section, the Court of Wards shall be guided by the provisions of`
  line `the Guardians and Wards Act, 1890 (VIII of 1890); and every guardian so appointed shall have, and be`
  line `subject to, the same rights, duties and liabilities as if he had been appointed under that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (71459)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Withdrawal to be notified in Gazette.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71459&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Where the Court of Wards withdraw its superintendence`
  line `from any person or property under this Act, the fact of such withdrawal shall be notified in the Local official`
  line Gazette.
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (71460)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71460&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `An appeal shall lie from every order passed under this Act, whether original or on`
  line appeal,--
  line
  line `(a) if the order is that of a Commissioner, to the Local Government;`
  line
  line `(b) if the order is that of a Deputy Commissioner, to the Commissioner;`
  line
  line `(c) in all other cases, to the Deputy Commissioner:`
  line
  line `Provided that in no case shall a third appeal lie.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (71461)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Control of Local Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71461&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `All orders or proceedings under this Act shall be subject to the`
  line `supervision and control of the Local Government; and the Local Government may, if it thinks fit, revise,`
  line `modify or reverse any such order or proceeding, whether an appeal is presented against any such order or`
  line `proceeding or not.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (71462)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Exercise of discretion not to be questioned in Civil Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71462&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `No suit shall be brought in any`
  line `Civil Court in respect of the exercise of any discretion conferred by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (71463)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Power for Local Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420&sectionId=71463&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_189924_1668661247420
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Local Government may make rules to`
  line `carry out the purposes and objects of this Act.`
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may--`
  line
  line `(a) prescribe the matters to which regard should be had in appointing or removing guardians and`
  line `managers, and in fixing their remuneration;`
  line
  line `(b) regulate the amount of security to be given by managers;`
  line
  line `(c) prescribe the cases in which proposals or arrangements connected with the administration of the`
  line `properties of Government wards shall be reported for the sanction of the Local Government;`
  line
  line `(d) prescribe the accounts and other returns which, and the periods and form at and in which, they`
  line `shall be rendered to the Court of Wards and by the Court of Wards to the Local Government;`
  line
  line `(e) regulate the custody of securities and title-deeds belonging to the estate or property of a`
  line `Government ward;`
  line
  line `(f) regulate the procedure in inquiries by, and in appeals from orders of, the Court of Wards under`
  line `this Act, and fix the periods of limitation which shall apply to such appeals;`
  line
  line `(g) confer upon the Court of Wards for the purposes of this Act any of the powers exercised by a`
  line `Civil Court in the trial of suits;`
  line
  line `(h) prescribe the mode in which powers delegated to managers are to be notified for the information`
  line `of persons concerned; and`
  line
  line `(i) generally prescribe the manner in which the powers and duties of the Court of Wards under this`
  line `Act shall be exercised and performed.`
  line
  line `(3) All rules made under this section shall be published in the Local official Gazette, and shall on such`
  line `publication have effect as if enacted by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
